# Local env for `wrangler dev` in workers/api. Copy to `.dev.vars` (done for
# you by `pnpm setup`); `.dev.vars` is gitignored and never committed.
# Keep in sync with `apiEnvSchema` in packages/core/src/env.ts and docs/secrets.md.

# Which environment this isolate believes it is in ("local" | "preview" | "prod").
ENVIRONMENT=local

# The local Hyperdrive->Postgres connection string does NOT go here — wrangler
# ignores it in .dev.vars. It lives in this directory's `.env` (see .env.example).

# Clerk credentials — optional until Epic #4 lands auth; uncomment and fill in
# real test-instance keys to exercise authenticated flows locally.
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_placeholder
# CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_placeholder
# PII field-encryption keyring (issue #47) — dev-only values, safe to commit
# because they never protect real data. Generate real keys with
# `openssl rand -base64 32`. PII_ENCRYPTION_KEYS maps key version -> base64
# 32-byte AES key (highest version encrypts new writes; keep old versions
# while rows encrypted with them exist). PII_HASH_KEY is separate and must
# not be rotated casually — rotating it orphans every stored value_hash.
PII_ENCRYPTION_KEYS={"1":"JB0/YtR2n0wh265yN8SRYBs45Lp0yt7sE2m+Ty6LOaE="}
PII_HASH_KEY=JKTMICa0vU/Ori8626X0AqH4D+At4aJ3cPg5JQBKqwI=
